records.addlTxt: Defendant appeared with counsel Nicholas Layland.  Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant will be waiving right to preliminary hearing.  Judge questions defendant regarding right to preliminary hearing.  Court finds she freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waives her right to a preliminary hearing.  DA states the Information will be filed during the hearing and reflects the same charges as in original complaint.  Court reviews those charges and penatlies with defendant.  Defense wishes to proceed to arraignment/plea/sentencing and waives the reading of the Information.  There is a joint recommendation that the defendant pleads to both counts and will enter into a diversion agreement on count 2.  Plea to count 1 - guilty; plea to count 2 - guilty.  Court reviews the plea questionnaire/waiver of rights/elements/diversion agreement with defendant.  Court makes written correction on diversion agreement as agreed to by parties.  Defense stipulates to factual basis for pleas.  Court finds the defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently entered pleas and waived her rights.  Court finds defendant guilty of Count 2 and withholds finding on Count 1.  Joint recommendation for Count 2 of probation with conditions.  Court accepts joint recommendation and orders on Count 2 sentence is withheld and placed on 1 year probation with the following conditions:  Must undergo a risk and needs assessment (COMPAS) and must comply with any recommendations; must sign releases of information for agent to verify compliance with programming/counseling; must continue to comply with conditions of bond on Count 1; must pay costs of the action and supervision.  Court accepts the Drug Treatment Diversion Agreement and count 1 will remain open during the terms of the agreement.  Judge reminds defendant of conditions of bond.  Information is filed before hearing completed.  (Copies of the amended Drug Treatment Diversion Agreement were given to attorney Layland and his client.)
Subpoena and Certificate of Appearance served on Adam Olson to appear at 2/26/15 preliminary hearing.

ADA Inlow appeared on behalf of the State.  Defendant appeared through her attorney, Nicholas Layland.  Defendant was unable to come to court today.  ADA Inlow requests the case be set for a preliminary hearing.
